A major pet food manufacturer, Menu Foods, recalled millions of containers of wet pet food due to reports of kidney failure and deaths in cats and dogs.
The company, based in Canada, produces over 1 billion containers annually for various store brands.
Concerned pet owners across North America were urged to check their cupboards for the affected products.
The recall included multiple brands of dog and cat food sold in cans and pouches.
The company identified a potential issue with wheat gluten sourced from a new supplier.
The FDA initiated an investigation following reports of pet illnesses and deaths.
